      "turn": 1,
      "actor": "gsd-phase-researcher",
      "content": "You are the subagent: gsd-phase-researcher. You must fulfill this research task and report findings.\n\n## CRITICAL CONTEXT\nThis is the Hivemind harness project. Phases 24.3.2 and 24.3.3 are actually COMPLETE (code exists and typecheck passes):\n- src/tools/session/execute-slash-command.ts (497 LOC) — complete with Zod schema, typed errors, commandSource tracking, execution tracking, two-stage routing, semantic agent selection\n- src/tools/session/resolve-command.ts (175 LOC) — command discovery + fuzzy matching + 5s cache\n- src/tools/session/dispatch-command.ts (94 LOC) — dispatch + agent validation\n- src/tools/session/semantic-agent-selector.ts (112 LOC) — keyword + fuzzy + interactive prompt\n- src/tools/session/validate-command.ts (47 LOC) — DEAD CODE (zero callers)\n- src/tools/session/workflow-parser.ts (79 LOC) — STUB (parser only, execution deferred)\n\n## RESEARCH SCOPE\nResearch what needs to happen between the current state (P24.3 complete) and P24.4 (References & Templates) to build a **routing system** that bridges:\n\n1. **NL Auto-Append Gap**: Currently, agents can use execute-slash-command tool, but there's no mechanism for agents to AUTOMATICALLY detect when a user's natural language matches a slash command and auto-append it. Research: How does OpenCode's session.prompt() work for this? What patterns exist for agents to auto-dispatch commands based on NL intent?\n\n2. **TUI Append Confusion**: After appendPrompt + submitPrompt, agents hallucinate that the command was already carried out. Research: What mechanism can we use to make agents aware that dispatching a command is NOT executing it?\n\n3. **validate-command.ts is dead code** (zero callers). Research: Where should contract validation be wired into the pipeline?\n\n4. **Subtask awareness for child sessions**: When execute-slash-command detects isChildSession (line 374), it bypasses TUI and uses dispatchCommand directly. But agents don't know they're in a child session. Research: How should subtask context propagate?\n\n5. **References & Templates System**: What should `.hivemind/references/` and `.hivemind/templates/` look like? Research GSD's reference/template patterns from the packed XML at `/Users/apple/hivemind-plugin-private/.hivemind/research/gsd-repo-packed.xml`\n\n6. **GSD CommandRoutingHub pattern**: Research the GSD routing pattern (command-aliases.cjs → command-routing-hub.cjs → per-family adapters) for how it could inform Hivemind's routing architecture.\n\n## FILES TO READ\n- /Users/apple/hivemind-plugin-private/src/tools/session/execute-slash-command.ts\n- /Users/apple/hivemind-plugin-private/src/tools/session/resolve-command.ts\n- /Users/apple/hivemind-plugin-private/src/tools/session/semantic-agent-selector.ts\n- /Users/apple/hivemind-plugin-private/src/tools/session/dispatch-command.ts\n- /Users/apple/hivemind-plugin-private/src/tools/session/validate-command.ts\n- /Users/apple/hivemind-plugin-private/src/tools/session/index.ts\n- /Users/apple/hivemind-plugin-private/.hivemind/research/gsd-repo-packed.xml (focus on command-routing-hub.cjs and command-aliases.cjs sections)\n- /Users/apple/hivemind-plugin-private/.planning/phases/24.3.2-revamp-execute-slash-command/\n- /Users/apple/hivemind-plugin-private/.planning/phases/24.3.3-namespace-routing-advanced-features/\n- /Users/apple/hivemind-plugin-private/.hivemind/planning/merged-phase-24.3-commands-infrastructure-2026-05-27/\n\n## OUTPUT\nWrite research findings to: .planning/research/p24.3-p24.4-routing-gaps-2026-05-27.md\n\nThe file must contain:\n1. **Gap Analysis**: Each of the 6 gaps with code evidence and severity (CRITICAL/HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW)\n2. **GSD Routing Pattern Analysis**: What Hivemind can adopt from GSD's CommandRoutingHub pattern\n3. **Wire-up Recommendations**: How to connect validate-command.ts into the pipeline\n4. **NL Auto-Append Architecture**: How agents should detect and auto-dispatch commands\n5. **Phase Recommendation**: What phases should be created/merged to address these gaps\n\n## SUCCESS CRITERIA\n- [ ] Research file written to .planning/research/p24.3-p24.4-routing-gaps-2026-05-27.md\n- [ ] All 6 gaps analyzed with code evidence\n- [ ] GSD routing patterns documented\n- [ ] Concrete phase recommendations\n",
